reviewText: I have this movie on one of the multi-movie combo sets - 10 ole 1930s John Wayne flicks on 2 disks. It was my least favorite of the 10. By the way, since the story seems to be entirely set in Indian Territory - aka Oklahoma - I have no idea where they came up with the title.

I loved both of these movies. 'Neath the Arizona Skies with John Wayne has a lot of action like all of his other movies. I would recommend this movie to any Western movie lover.
Border Caballero was a surprisingly good movie with Tim McCoy as a bonus movie.

I have reviewed 3 or 4 copies of this film and I find the one most easily to watch is the Platinum / Echobridge product listed. I even compared it to the achhive  more expensive dvds which in my opinoin
I would stay away from.
